  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build School Toilets To Save Lives And End Poverty</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at providing adequate toilet facilities and clean, potable water to the 1000 pupils who attend Abiola Nursery and Primary School, a low-income school in Mushin (a slum) in Lagos State, and in the process save lives, improve child health, ensure greater dignity, privacy, and personal safety, particularly for girls. We hope to build a toilet facility comprising 5 well-equipped toilet stalls and also install a borehole that will enable pupils get easy access to clean water.</narrative>
  </description>
